title: Basketball: Much back in OC, transfers to JSerra
text:
Â· posted by STEVE FRYER 
Sebastian Much, a 6-foot-7 junior, transferred to JSerra, JSerra athletic director Brett Kay confirmed today. 
Much was a key player last season at Archbishop Mitty of San Jose, which lost to La Mirada in a CIF State championship game. He is an excellent shooter. 
Much was at St. Margaret's his freshman year. A Contra Costa Times report quoted Much's mother saying the move back to Orange County was for parental job opportunity reasons. 
I saw Much play in that state championship game. He is fluid and a fine shooter. More from Blog: OC Varsity
